article.description: Chandi Jones netted 28 points as Houston topped UW-Green Bay for its first NCAA win.
article.headline: Jones scores 28 to lead Cougers
article.linkText: Houston trails at half but beats Wisconsin-Green Bay
article.story:
SANTA BARBARA, California (Ticker) -- Chandi Jones scored 28 
points to lead third-seeded Houston to a 62-47 victory over No.
14 Wisconsin-Green Bay in the opening round of the East Region.

The Lady Cougars (28-3), who have won a school-record 13
straight games, erased a two-point halftime deficit by holding
the Phoenix to just 20 points in the second half, earning their
first NCAA Tournament win.

Jones, the third-leading scorer in the nation with a 22.5
average this season, nailed 4-of-8 attempts from 3-point range.
The 5-10 senior and Sancho Lyttle combined to score all the
points for Houston during a 14-7 run that left the Lady Cougars
on top, 55-43, with 3:37 remaining.

Nicole Oliver chipped in 11 points and Lyttle pulled down 10
rebounds for the Houston, which will meet the winner of the
UC-Santa Barbara-Colorado game on Monday.

Nicole Soulis scored 13 points and Amy Fieck had a game-high 11
rebounds for Wisconsin-Green Bay (23-8), which hit just 7-of-29
shots (24 percent) from the floor in the second half and shot 29
percent overall.
